const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit);

res.json({ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } });
```

Key behaviours verified by the test run:
| Scenario | Result |
|---|---|
| Default (no params) | 10 items, page=1, total=15, totalPages=2 ✅ |
| `?page=2&limit=10` | 5 items on second page ✅ |
| `?limit=5` | 5 items, totalPages=3 ✅ |
| `?page=100` (out of range) | empty `data: []`, page=100 ✅ |
| `GET /users/:id` (existing) | untouched, still works ✅ |

